<br>
Still out of the ideas listed above there are a few gems. =)<br>
<br>
A lesser mod rod.  Sounds like a very good idea.  And the ability to cast and have the spell end up on someone else's cursor.  Another great idea.  I hope both of these are put in the game.   <br>
<br>
More pet affecting spells..  Actually I'd change that to simply more things that effect the pet.  We all know the problem, we get a pet spell, it's of X level.   And it's forever going to be only X powerful.  They simply don't scale.  Instead we get a few more new versions of burnout which hardly suffice, and turn our pets into rapid attacking machine guns.  Personally I'd perfer they start hitting harder and less often.  I could do with less battle spam.   We need some spells and items that help our pets scale with each expansion.  I'd suggest breaking down the abilities and spells to augment pet abilities, and perhaps only work for a certain type of element.   A focus item that makes earth elementals have 10% more HP for instance.  Or allow greater fire pets to cast slightly higher level spells.  etc.<br>
<br>
For new pet spells.  I've actually been wanting Genie pets for a while now.  I think they should be given the air genie and the fire genie models respectively.  Add in 2 more skins for earth and water and you are set.  <br>
<br>
Personally I'd like to see them as a sort of support pet, where they either wouldn't attack at all, or not be too effective at attacking.  And they could either mess enemies up more, or add to some raiding features.  Hmm cast a buff on the genie and they go around and cast the same buff on two more people who don't have it yet.  Adding in the 3 wishes or favors traditional to them would be nice as well.  Perhaps they can perform 3 decent abilities before disappearing.  And they would cost an expensive component to summon.  <br>
<br>
Although the above would be cool I feel guiltly as hell asking for something like this.  Consider the wizard.  Although he can out nuke us a bit for most levels, and by a signifigant margin for higher levels, how would he compare now with a class that has this much utility and can nuke pretty decently?<br>
<br>
Heh anyway.  I love ideas, keep em coming. =) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ueuphorion.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Euphorion</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 29<br> <font color=#333333>(5/8/02 10:34:08 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=154.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_lightbulb.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: New ideas. =)</span><hr size=1> Well, I like many of the ideas, knowing well I will hardly ever see any/mnost of them implemented.<br>
And I also know that probably preferences change depending what lvl you are.<br>
<br>
But what I currently (lvl 36) would like to see most, would be some self-only-tp-spells. ;-)<br>
Couldn't we get Some &quot;Summon Staff of Antonica/Velious/Faydwer/Odus&quot; at around lvl 30 or 40? It could be no drop and only allows to teleport to 4 locations: the 4 Luclin Spires. <br>
I know I would definately love it ;-)<br>
<br>
So we couldn't take away &quot;business&quot; from the wizards or druids, but who says that Magicians, who are conjurers, shouldn't be able to summon some item that has 1 charge of a tp-spell?<br>
<br>
I would even like it if it would cost some &quot;insane&quot; amount of mana to cast it (500+)<br>
<br>
